===Talking to any of King's men at the temple===
* '''Player:''' Okay, how are we looking?
* '''Nezketi:''' This isn't good, iknami. We don't think there's any way we can put this egg back together again.
* '''Player:''' What are we going to do?
* '''Acatzin:''' The way I see it, we only have one option. We need to replace the egg.
* '''Player:''' Replace Pumpty Lumpty? That's madness!
* '''Kauayotl:''' It's more than madness. There isn't even a word to properly describe what it is. However, I fear it is the only path available to us.
* '''Player:''' But where would we even get a replacement egg?
* '''Acatzin:''' We're going to need to obtain a chicken egg.
* '''Nezketi:''' Tetamo! That's preposterous! A chicken egg is far too small.
* '''Acatzin:''' Not if it's from a rather large chicken.
* '''Kauayotl:''' A dragon egg is what we need. They are the perfect size.
* '''Nezketi:''' A dragon egg would be suicide. No dragon would willingly give up its egg. What we need is a jaguar egg.
* '''Kauayotl:''' But jaguars don't lay eggs...
* '''Player:''' How about we gather a few potential eggs and pick the best one?
* '''Acatzin:''' Kuani! What a brilliant idea.
* '''Player:''' Okay, I just need to know where I can find these eggs.
* '''Kauayotl:''' There are some dragons in a cave just south east of here, across the river from Tal Teklan. One of them should have an egg.
* '''Acatzin:''' There's a chicken farm on the outskirts of Tal Teklan. I reckon you'll be able to find a large chicken egg there.
* '''Nezketi:''' And I've heard talk of some eggs in an old camp site by the mine east of Tal Teklan. Apparently the camp site is a hot spot for jaguars! They must be jaguar eggs!
* '''Player:''' Right then. I'll be back once I have some eggs.
* {{tact|end}}

